DISTRIBUTION STRATEGY: INVESTING WHERE IT MATTERS
Monthly Business Review | March 2026

Differentiated channel investment to protect client retention, sustain brand health, and optimize long-term ROI

CURRENT BUSINESS CHALLENGES


Specialty Store Closures — Accelerating retail contraction reduces high-touch points; clients are migrating to open-sell and DTC with no guided transition plan.


Open-Sell Expertise Gap — Untrained associates cannot convey the value of prestige formulations, eroding brand perception at the shelf and depressing conversion on high-price-point SKUs.


Over-Assorted Low-Volume Doors — Wide distribution with thin sell-through creates chronic stockouts and customer disappointment, diluting brand equity with no commensurate return.


Resource Strain — Fixed budgets spread across too many activations and staffing commitments yield diminishing ROI; high-performing doors are under-resourced while low-performers absorb spend.

STRATEGIC IMPERATIVE


Shift from uniform coverage to tiered investment — concentrate resources in channels that deliver the richest client experience and the strongest lifetime value.

CHANNEL-DIFFERENTIATED STRATEGY

BRAND BOUTIQUES — FLAGSHIP EXPERIENCE
Full assortment + exclusive launches and limited editions
1-to-1 consultations, loyalty tier upgrades, VIP events
Premium CRM journeys: personalized replenishment, birthday rituals, early access
Highest staffing and activation investment — anchor of brand storytelling

SPECIALTY RETAIL — CURATED PARTNERSHIP
Edited hero assortment aligned to door-level sell-through data
Co-branded activations and seasonal gift-with-purchase programs
Shared CRM touchpoints; in-store education sessions to build associate advocacy
Tiered support: prioritize top-performing doors; right-size or exit low-ROI locations

OPEN-SELL — GUIDED DISCOVERY
Streamlined core SKU set — minimize stockout risk and reduce planogram complexity
Point-of-sale collateral and digital QR education to bridge the expertise gap
Sampling-led GWP strategy to drive trial; lower-barrier entry price points
Lighter staffing model offset by strong visual merchandising and digital support

CLIENT LIFECYCLE CONTINUITY
Unified loyalty program across channels ensures clients who shift from closed specialty doors to open-sell or DTC retain status, points, and personalized benefits — preventing attrition during transition.

Confidential — For Internal Use Only
Prioritize experience. Invest with precision. Protect the client relationship.

